    <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
      <body>
        <div rend="parallel">
          <lg xml:id="Aink409">
            <l>putalvaṟ kavaiiyiṉaṉ ṟantai meṉmoḻip</l>
            <l>putalvaṉ ṟāyō viruvaruṅ kavaiyiṉa</l>
            <l>ḷiṉitu maṉṟavavar kiṭakkai</l>
            <l>naṉiyirum parappiṉiv vulakuṭa ṉuṟumē</l>
          </lg>
          <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The father embraced [his] son,</l>
<l>[and] the mother of the softly spoken son embraced them both.</l>
<l>It is so sweet, their repose, equal to this world</l>
<l>equal to this world of a most vast<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">This rather clunky phrase is my attempt to retain the flavour of the instensifer <q xml:lang="ta-Latn"><hi rend="italic">naṉi</hi></q>, which qualifies <q xml:lang="ta-Latn"><hi rend="italic">irum</hi></q> ('big, dark').</note> expanse.</l>
          </lg>
        </div>
      </body>
    </text>
